commit.message: Fix misspelling in README.md

biosdisk: Use `genisoimage` over `mkisoimage`

The binaries below are included in the Debian package *genisoimage* [1],
`mkisoimage` is not one of them, so use `genisoimage`.

	/usr/bin/devdump
	/usr/bin/dirsplit
	/usr/bin/genisoimage
	/usr/bin/geteltorito
	/usr/bin/isodump
	/usr/bin/isoinfo
	/usr/bin/isovfy
	/usr/bin/mkzftree

[1]: https://packages.debian.org/sid/amd64/genisoimage/filelist

commit.message: Create a README
add debian packaging
Switch install.sh to a proper Makefile
Add me to AUTHORS
update man page

Remove remaining install dependencies

The ones left are now runtime checks instead
Handle filenames with multiple periods
fix uninstall command
set make image flag to 0 by default

Drop unnecessary legacy content

The path is much simpler now, most of the stuff to build packages
and unnecessary logic cruft can be removed

Drop blconf script

Effectively all major distros either use GRUB2 for their legacy
installations.

Instead install a GRUB2 configuration file to use

Drop support for trying to generate distro specific packages

It doesn't make sense to package up a BIOS release in deb/rpm.
Just use biosdisk to build it into an image and install it to
the system.
remove changelog files, metadata is in VSC now
Remove VERSION, will tag on github instead
remove TODO, most of it won't be done
Add a warning for EFI mode
